## Windrose Mod Manager v0.5.2

Windrose Mod Manager v0.5.2 is a polish and trust update on top of v0.5.1. It keeps the new Dashboard/FTP work and tightens the daily workflow around compare, sync review, hosted path diagnostics, and startup reliability.

### Highlights

- Dashboard compare now has its own target selector for Local Server, Dedicated Server, and Hosted Server.
- Dashboard `Run Compare` updates the parity card for the selected target without forcing a tab jump.
- Added `Review Sync Actions` after compare for safe, preview-first client-to-server fixes.
- Local and Dedicated sync actions install missing client mods through the existing backup/history install path.
- Hosted sync actions upload missing client mods through the existing hosted deployment path.
- Server-only / hosted-only removals are shown for review, but are not auto-deleted.
- Manifest drift is now surfaced on the Dashboard instead of only being logged.
- Activity / Backups wording is aligned across the app instead of referring to the old Recovery tab name.
- Activity refresh is lighter for large histories, and non-visible Activity refreshes are avoided where safe.
- Startup/discovery is safer when an old saved Steam path points to a missing or inaccessible drive.
- FTP path checks now handle servers that do not support `SIZE` by falling back to parent-directory listing.
- Hosted path errors now explain FTP-root-relative paths, including Nitrado-style setups.
- Hosted setup retains provider QoL for Host Havoc and Indifferent Broccoli.

### Safety Fixes

- Failed hosted Dashboard sync no longer records a successful hosted upload in Activity.
- Dashboard status coloring no longer treats `Not running` as a healthy/running state.
- Missing remote root, mods folder, save root, or ServerDescription paths now produce clearer path guidance.

### Compatibility

- Existing v0.5.1 hosted FTP/SFTP profiles remain compatible.
- Existing older SFTP hosted profiles without a protocol field still default to SFTP.
- Existing hosted backup/recovery records using old `sftp://...` identity remain compatible.
- FTP remains file-transfer only; restart-command automation still requires SFTP/SSH-style command access.

### Validation

- `python -m compileall windrose_deployer`
- `python -m pytest -q --basetemp .pytest_tmp_full_052_release -o cache_dir=.pytest_cache_full_052_release` -> `171 passed`
- `git diff --check` -> clean except normal CRLF warnings

